Model to correct for coverage

### Asymptotic model
mydonors = unique(hsc$Donor)
model_list = list()
model_function_list = list()
hsc_newmut_list = list()
for (i in 1:length(mydonors)){
  m4 = subset(hsc, Donor==mydonors[i] & meandp < 50) ## at very high dp, get errors
  m4sorted = sortedXyData(m4$meandp, m4$Nmut)
  model.as = NLSstAsymptotic(m4sorted)
  model_list[[i]] = model.as
  
  model_function = function(x, model.as){
    b0 = model.as[1]
    b1 = model.as[2]
    lrc = model.as[3]
    b0 + b1*(1-exp(-exp(lrc) * x))  
  }

  myrange=1:round(max(m4$meandp))
  asp = data.frame(x=myrange, y=unlist(lapply(myrange, FUN=model_function, model.as=model_list[[i]] )))
  ggplot(m4) +
    geom_point(aes(x=meandp,y=Nmut), data=m4, alpha=0.3) + 
    scale_fill_brewer(type="qual", palette=3) + 
    ylab("# Mutations") +
    xlab("Coverage per colony")+
    geom_line(aes(x=x, y=y), data=asp)+
    ggtitle(paste(mydonors[i],": uncorrected burden",sep="") )+
    theme_bw()
  ggsave(file=paste("figures/hsc_uncorrected_burden_by_depth.",mydonors[i],".pdf", sep=""), width=4.5,height=4)
  
  new_nmut = function(rd, nmut){  ## correction to 30dp
    nmut + ( model_function(30, model.as=model_list[[i]]) - model_function(rd, model.as=model_list[[i]] ))
  }
  m4$Nmut_emily_as = apply(m4, MARGIN=1, FUN=function(X)  new_nmut(rd=as.numeric(X[which(colnames(m4)=="meandp")]), nmut=as.numeric(X[which(colnames(m4)=="Nmut")]) ) )
  hsc_newmut_list[[i]] = m4
  ggplot(m4) +
    geom_point(aes(meandp,Nmut_emily_as), alpha=0.3) + 
    ylab("# Mutations") +
    xlab("Coverage per colony")+
    ggtitle(paste(mydonors[i],": corrected burden",sep="") )+
    theme_bw()
  ggsave(file=paste("figures/hsc_corrected_burden_by_depth.",mydonors[i],".pdf", sep=""), width=4.5,height=4)
}
write.table(data.frame(Donor=mydonors, do.call(rbind, model_list) ), file="fullHSC_asymptotic_correction_model_parameters.txt", col.names=T, row.names=F, quote=F)

# Indel correction ## Model to correct for coverage

### Asymptotic model
mydonors = c("AX001","KX001","KX002","KX003","CB001")

model_list = list()
model_function_list = list()
hsc_newmut_list = list()
for (i in 1:length(mydonors)){
  m4 = subset(hsc, Donor==mydonors[i] & meandp < 50) ## at very high dp, get errors
  m4sorted = sortedXyData(m4$meandp, m4$Nmut_indel)
  model.as = NLSstAsymptotic(m4sorted)
  model_list[[i]] = model.as
  
  
  model_function = function(x, model.as){
    b0 = model.as[1]
    b1 = model.as[2]
    lrc = model.as[3]
    b0 + b1*(1-exp(-exp(lrc) * x))  
  }

  myrange=1:round(max(m4$meandp))
  asp = data.frame(x=myrange, y=unlist(lapply(myrange, FUN=model_function, model.as=model_list[[i]] )))
  ggplot(m4) +
    geom_point(aes(x=meandp,y=Nmut_indel), data=m4, alpha=0.3) + 
    scale_fill_brewer(type="qual", palette=3) + 
    ylab("# Indels") +
    xlab("Coverage per colony")+
    geom_line(aes(x=x, y=y), data=asp)+
    ggtitle(paste(mydonors[i],": uncorrected burden",sep="") )+
    theme_bw()
  ggsave(file=paste("figures/hsc_uncorrected_burden_by_depth_indel.",mydonors[i],".pdf", sep=""), width=4.5,height=4)
  
  new_nmut = function(rd, nmut){  ## correction to 30dp
    nmut + ( model_function(30, model.as=model_list[[i]]) - model_function(rd, model.as=model_list[[i]] ))
  }
  m4$Nmut_emily_as = apply(m4, MARGIN=1, FUN=function(X)  new_nmut(rd=as.numeric(X[which(colnames(m4)=="meandp")]), nmut=as.numeric(X[which(colnames(m4)=="Nmut")]) ) )
  hsc_newmut_list[[i]] = m4
  ggplot(m4) +
    geom_point(aes(meandp,Nmut_emily_as), alpha=0.3) + 
    ylab("# Indels") +
    xlab("Coverage per colony")+
    ggtitle(paste(mydonors[i],": corrected burden",sep="") )+
    theme_bw()
  ggsave(file=paste("figures/hsc_corrected_burden_by_depth_indel",mydonors[i],".pdf", sep=""), width=4.5,height=4)
}
write.table(data.frame(Donor=mydonors, do.call(rbind, model_list) ), file="fullHSC_asymptotic_correction_model_parameters_indel.txt", col.names=T, row.names=F, quote=F)
